23 countries recently met in Greenland to encourage governments to act on global warming instead of arguing.
Worldwide, countries are agreeing that the U.N.
Kyoto Protocol, which commits 39 nations to reduce greenhouse gases, is not enough.
Infrastructure in Russia is being damaged due to the melting permafrost including airports, gas pipelines and railways.
